quran[11]{c,v,t,f}:
  92,19,"not as payment for any favours that he received,"
  92,20,"but only to seek the good pleasure of his Lord Most High.{1}",1:[This is further explanation of the sincerity of the pious man. He was not indebted in any way to the people on whom he spends his wealth so that he may be doing so in order to repay for favors received]
  92,21,"He will surely be well-pleased (with him).{1}",1:[This verse can have two meanings and both are correct:]
  96,7,"for he believes himself to be self-sufficient.{1}",1:[That is, when the man has attained wealth, honor and rank and whatever else he desired to attain in the world, he becomes rebellious instead of being grateful and transgresses the boundaries of servitude to Allah.]
  96,8,"Surely to your Lord is your return.{1}",1:[That is, whatever he might have attained in the world, which makes him behave arrogantly and rebelliously, in the end he has to return to your Lord. Then he will realize what fate awaits him in consequence of his such attitude and behavior.]
  96,9,"Did you see him who forbids"
  97,4,"The angels along with the Spirit{1} descend in it by the permission of their Lord{2} with all kinds of decrees.",1:[The Spirit: Gabriel, who has been mentioned separately from the angels in view of his unique eminence, honor and merit.],2:[That is, they do not descend of their own accord but by leave of their Lord, and every decree implies amr hakim (a wise decree) as described in (Surah Ad-Dukhan, Ayat 5).]
  97,5,"All peace is that night until the rise of dawn.{1}",1:[That is, the entire night, from evening till morning, is peace, free from every evil and mischief.]
  98,1,"Those who disbelieved{1} – be they from the People of the Book or from those who associated{2} others with Allah in His Divinity – will not desist from unbelief until the Clear Proof should come to them;{3}",1:[Here the word kufr],2:[(unbelief) has been used],3:[in its widest]
  98,2,"a Messenger{1} from Allah, reciting from Purified Scrolls;{2}",1:[Here, the Prophet (peace be],2:[upon him) has been called]
  98,3,"in writings wherein are scriptures, absolutely true and unerring."
